          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Musk attacks USAID</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-feb-4-1.png" alt="Musk attacks USAID" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Elon Musk and the US Agency for International Development (USAID) headquarters. Credits: Salon/Getty Images
          </p>
        </mj-text>

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Musk calls for USAID removal after DOGE gains access to restricted areas. Lawmakers condemn his influence.</strong></p> 

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Elon Musk, who leads the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h1-1-called-for-dismantling" target="_blank">called for dismantling</a> USAID and called it a “criminal organization.” This call comes after the suspension of two USAID security officials who denied DOGE personnel access to classified areas. DOGE gained entry despite resistance. This incident has raised multiple concerns about security breaches, as Elon Musk is not an elected official.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Meanwhile, Trump has paused <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h1-2-us-foreign-aid-for-90-days" target="_blank">US foreign aid for 90 days</a>, impacting programs worldwide. On Saturday, the USAID website went offline, and a barebones page for the agency appeared on the Department of State website.  Nearly 100 USAID employees have been <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h1-3-put-on-leave" target="_blank">put on leave</a>. Musk also announced an <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h1-4-end-to-us-funding" target="_blank">end to US funding</a> for South Africa, coincidentally his home country, over land confiscation policies.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Lawmakers, including Senator Chris Coons and Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, have condemned Musk’s influence and the administration’s moves. Former USAID officials warn that dismantling the agency without congressional approval would be unconstitutional. US AID has missions in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h1-5-over-100-countries" target="_blank">over 100 countries</a>, mainly assisting with disaster relief, poverty eradication, and democratic reforms.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
 
 
