          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Bi-lateral talks over dinner</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-feb-4-2.png" alt="Bi-lateral talks over dinner" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            The two leaders pictured following the signing of the Abraham Accords in 2020. Credits: Reuters
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: President Trump will host Benjamin Netanyahu in the White House, making him the first foreign guest for his term.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will meet President Trump in DC today. The two heads of state will <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h2-6-meet-for-dinner" target="_blank">meet for dinner</a>. This meeting happens as indirect talks are slated to resume between Israel and Hamas on the second stage of the three-phase Gaza ceasefire and hostage release deal. The discussions will focus on the Gaza ceasefire, hostages, and Israel-Saudi normalization.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump is a strong supporter of Israel. He moved the US embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem during his term of the presidency. He has also taken <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h2-7-credit-for-ceasefire-deal" target="_blank">credit for the ceasefire deal</a> between Israel and Hamas. Netanyahu is facing internal pressure from his political allies to continue military operations, which has led to some fighting within the Israeli right wing.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump heavily <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h2-8-prioritized-us-israel-relations" target="_blank">prioritized US-Israel relations</a>, reversing some Biden-era policies. His meeting with Netanyahu will be his first meeting with a foreign official during his new term. “I think it’s a testimony to the strength of the Israeli-American alliance,” said Netanyahu. His visit includes meetings with US officials and Congress and media appearances.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
