        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Rubio demands Panama</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: US Secretary of State Macrco Runio has a home in Panama to attempt to reduce Chinese influence on the Panama Canal.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Marco Rubio demanded that Panama <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h23-9-reduce-china-influence" target="_blank">reduce China’s influence</a> over the Panama Canal or face American action. His warning follows President Trump’s controversial vow to “retake” the canal, citing unproven claims of Chinese military presence and unfair shipping fees. The Panamanian government owns and operates the waterway under a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h3-10-neutrality-treaty" target="_blank">neutrality treaty</a> signed with the US decades ago.
      </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Panamanian President Jose Raul Mulino said he would not renew a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h3-11-belt-and-road-initiative-agreement" target="_blank">Belt Road Initiative agreement</a> with China signed by a former president in 2017. He also rejected any discussion of canal ownership but proposed technical talks to address US concerns. However, Chinese companies have invested in ports and terminals near the canal, which Trump is concerned about.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Trump’s rhetoric has sparked <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-02-2025-h3-12-protests-in-panama" target="_blank">protests in Panama</a>, with demonstrators denouncing the US interference. Flashbacks of American control and the 1989 invasion fuel local resistance. 
        Some Panamanians criticize their government for not fairly distributing canal profits. Many will likely blame the president for not extending the BRI deal to appeal to the US.
        </p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

